gurmukhi: ਜਯ ਜੰਪਤ ਜੁੱਪਤ ਜੁੱਗਣ ਜੂਹ ਜੁਅੰ || ਭੈ ਕੰਪਹਿ ਮੇਰੁ ਪਯਾਲ ਭੁਅੰ ||
transliteration: Jay Janpat Judgad Jooh Juan|| Bhai Kanpah(i) Mer(u) Payaal Bhuan||
translation: Gather ye together and shout victory to that Lord, in whose Fear tremble the heaven, nether-world and the earth.

gurmukhi: ਤਪੁ ਤਾਪਮ ਸਰਬ ਜਲੇ ਰੁ ਥਲੰ || ਧਨ ੳੁਚਰਤ ੲਿੰਦ੍ਰ ਕੁਬੇਰ ਬਲੰ ||੧||੧੪੧||
transliteration: Tap(u) Taapas Sarab Jale Ru Thalan|| Dhan Ouchrat Indra Kouber Balan||1||141||
translation: For whose realization all the ascetics of water and land perform austerities. To Whom Indra, Kuber and king Bal hail 1.141.

gurmukhi: ਅਨਖੇਦ ਸਰੂਪ ਅਭੇਦ ਅਭਿਅੰ || ਅਨਖੰਡ ਅਭੂਤ ਅਛੇਦ ਅਛਿਅੰ ||
transliteration: Ankhed Saroopabhed Abhian|| Ankhanndabhoot Achhed Achhian||
translation: He is Griefless Entity, Indiscriminate and Fearless. He is Indivisible, Elementless, Invincible and Indestructible.

gurmukhi: ਅਨਕਾਲ ਅਪਾਲ ਦੲਿਅਾਲ ਸੁਅੰ || ਜਿਹ ਠਟੀਅੰ ਮੇਰ ਅਾਕਾਮ ਭੁਅੰ ||੨||੧੪੨||
transliteration: Ankaal Apaal Daeaal Suan|| Jih Thatooan Mer Aakaas Bhuan||2||142||
translation: He is Deathless, Patronless, Beneficent and Self-Existent, Who hath established Sumeru, Heaven and Earth. 2.142.

gurmukhi: ਅਨਖੰਡ ਅਮੰਡ ਪ੍ਰਚੰਡ ਨਰੰ || ਜਿਹ ਰਚੀਅੰ ਦੇਵ ਬਰੰ ||
transliteration: Ankhanndamannd Prachanndd Naran|| Jih Rachooan Dev Adev Baran||
translation: He is non-divisible, non-stable and Mighty Purusha, Who hath Created great gods and demons.

gurmukhi: ਸਭ ਕੀਨੀ ਦੀਨ ਜਮੀਨ ਜਮਾਂ || ਜਿਹ ਰਚੀਅੰ ਸਰਬ ਮਕੀਨ ਮਕਾਂ ||੩||੧੪੩||
transliteration: Sabh Koonoo Doon Jamoond|| Jih Rachooan Sarab Makoon Makaan||3||143||
translation: Who hath Created both Earth and Sky. Who hath Created all the Universe and the objects of the universe. 3.143.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਹ ਰਾਗ ਨ ਰੂਪ ਨ ਰੇਖ ਨ ਰੁਖੰ || ਜਿਹ ਤਾਪ ਨ ਸ੍ਰਾਪ ਨ ਸੋਕ ਸੁਖੰ ||
transliteration: Jih Raag Na Roop Na Rekh Na Roukhan|| Jih Taap Na Sraap Na Sok Soukhan||
translation: He has no affection for any form, sign of face. He is without any effect of heat and curse and without grief and comfort.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਹ ਰੋਗ ਨ ਸੋਗ ਨ ਭੋਗ ਭਯੰ || ਜਿਹ ਖੇਦ ਨ ਭੇਦ ਨ ਛੇਦ ਛਯੰ ||੪||੧੪੪||
transliteration: Jih Rog Na Sog Na Bhog Bhuyan|| Jih Khed Na Bhed Na Chhed Chhayan||4||144||
translation: He is without ailment, sorrow, enjoyment and fear. He is without pain, without contrast, without jealousy, without thirst.4.144.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਹ ਜਾਤਿ ਨ ਪਾਤਿ ਨ ਮਾਤ ਪਿਤੰ || ਜਿਹ ਰਚੀਅੰ ਛਤ੍ਰੀ ਛਤ੍ਰ ਛਿਤੰ ||
transliteration: Jih Jaat(i) Na Paat(i) Na Maat Pitan|| Jih Rachooan Chhatroo Chhatra Chhitan||
translation: He is without caste, without caste, without lineage, without mother and father. He hast Created the Kshatriya warriors under royal canopies on the earth.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਹ ਰਾਗ ਨ ਰੇਖ ਨ ਰੋਗ ਭਣੰ || ਜਿਹ ਦ੍ਵੈਖ ਨ ਦਾਗ ਨ ਦੋਖ ਗਣੰ ||੫||੧੪੫||
transliteration: Jih Raag Na Rekh Na Rog Bhanan|| Jih Dvaikh Na Daag Na Dokh Gadan||5||145||
translation: He is said to be without affection, without lineage and ailment. He is considered without blemish, stain and malice. 5.145.

gurmukhi: ਜਿਹ ਅੰਡਹਿ ਤੇ ਬ੍ਹਿਮੰਡ ਰਚਿਓ || ਦਿਸ ਚਾਰ ਕਰੀ ਨਵ ਖੰਡ ਸਚਿਓ ||
transliteration: Jih Andah(i) Te Brah(i)mand Rachio|| Dis Chnr Daroo Nav Khanndsachio||
translation: He hath Created the Universe out of he Comic Egg. He hath Created forteen worlds and nine regions.

gurmukhi: ਰਜ ਤਾਮਸ ਤੇਜ ਅਤੇਜ ਕੀਓ || ਅਨਭੳੁ ਪਦ ਅਾਪ ਪ੍ਰਚੰਡ ਲੀਓ ||੬||੧੪੬||
transliteration: Raj Taamas Tej Atej Kooo|| Anbhau Pad Aap Prachanndd Looo||6||146||
translation: He hath Created Rajas (activity), Tamas (morbidity), light and darkness. And he Himself manifested His Mighty Resplendent Form. 6.146.

gurmukhi: ਸ੍ਰਿਅ ਸਿੰਧੁਰ ਬਿੰਧ ਨਗਿੰਦ ਨਗੰ || ਸ੍ਰਿਅ ਜੱਛ ਗੰਧਰਬ ਫਣਿੰਦ ਭੁਜੰ ||
transliteration: Sria Sindhur Bindh Nagind Nagadg|| Sria Jachchh Gaddharab Phanind Bhujan||
translation: He Created the ocean, Vindhyachal mountain and Sumeru mountain. He Created Yakshas, Gandharvas, Sheshanagas and serpents.
